CHILE DAYBOOK: Central Banker Speaks After Surprise Rate Rise

-- B y   R a n d y   W o o d s
-- 
2011-05-13T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/chile-daybook-central-banker-speaks-after-surprise-rate-rise.html
Chile  central bank board member
Enrique Marshall speaks at an event at the bank’s Santiago
headquarters at 10 a.m. New York time.  ECONOMY:
*The central bank raised its benchmark interest rate more than
expected amid concern that surging economic growth gives policy
makers no leeway to ease up on the current pace of tightening.
The five-member policy board raised the overnight rate by a
half-point to 5 percent, matching the forecast of four of 18
economists surveyed by Bloomberg. Fourteen analysts forecasted a
quarter-point increases to 4.75 percent.  EQUITIES:
*The Ipsa index rose 0.3 percent to 4,863.81.
*Besalco SA rose 2 percent to 938.23 pesos. The Chilean
engineering and construction company had its 12- to 18-month
price estimate increased to 1,130 pesos from 1,020 pesos at
Larrain Vial SA, which reiterated a “buy” recommendation.
*Parque Arauco SA gained 1.7 percent to 1,104.4 pesos. The
shopping mall operator replaced Cencosud SA in Banco Santander
SA’s list of top Chilean stock picks.
*Soc. Quimica y Minera de Chile SA fell 0.8 percent to 26,692
pesos. Chile’s largest fertilizer producer slid along with
declines in the price of some agricultural commodities.  MARKETS:
*Chile’s peso rose as recovering copper prices signaled a higher
 trade surplus  for the world’s biggest exporter of the metal. The
peso strengthened 0.4 percent to 466.35 per  U.S. dollar .
*The two-year interest-rate swap rate fell 5 basis points, or
0.05 percentage point, to 5.59 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
